  "texts": [
    "It reduces dimensionality and consists of two primary parts: an encoder and a decoder.",
    "The encoder converts the input data into code, or compressed data, which the decoder then rebuilds to create an output corresponding to the input.",
    "Convolution layers, or dense layers, are present in the encoder section.",
    "The encoding and decoding phases ought to be at comparable stages.",
    "The encoder increases the size of the data, but it also reduces it."
